    <p>The Mu­seum Roundtable Cel­e­brates Racial Har­mony Day</p>
    <p>This Racial Har­mony Day, which falls on July 21, the Mu­seum Roundtable cel­e­brates Sin­ga­pore’s eth­nic and cul­tural di­ver­sity through food. Learn how var­i­ous cuisines are made through il­lus­trated recipes and videos of dishes shared by the Mu­seum Roundtable mem­bers and win prizes when you visit the I Love Mu­se­ums Face­book page from Sun­day. The Mu­seum Roundtable was es­tab­lished by the Na­tional Her­itage Board in 1996 to pro­mote a mu­seum-go­ing cul­ture among Sin­ga­pore­ans and to po­si­tion mu­se­ums as unique cul­tural des­ti­na­tions.</p>
    <p>View it on www.face­book.com/ILoveMu­se­ums</p>
    <p>Sun to July 31</p>
    <p>Racial Har­mony Cel­e­bra­tions</p>
    <p>Ex­plore Sin­ga­pore’s di­ver­sity as a multi-eth­nic and multi-re­li­gious so­ci­ety at home with the #StayHomeCh­al­lenge se­ries pre­sented by the Sun Yat Sen Nanyang Me­mo­rial Hall in cel­e­bra­tion of Racial Har­mony Day, which falls on Tues­day .</p>
    <p>View it on www.face­book.com/sys­nmh</p>
    <p>Till Tues www.sys­nmh.org.sg/en</p>
    <p>poly:taire II – An On­line Multi-dis­ci­plinary Live Per­for­mance</p>
